I think Egon was carrying on Shador research, the mass of dishes and ariels on the house shows he was monitoring or looking for something...

snippet.textDisplay:
This trailer is absolutely amazing. It is everything that a lifelong Ghostbusters fan could have hoped for in a new movie. It respects the legacy of the original movies and characters without feeling that it needs to copy every beat from those storylines the way J.J. Abrams would. Unlike the recent Star Wars and Terminator sequels, it doesn't trash classic characters by killing them off. It actually does the opposite, it takes the character whose actor died in real life and makes him a central factor in this new storyline. The nods to the original music are absolutely wonderful. And the use of classic quotes and scenes are wisely kept to a minimum but extremely well-chosen and edited.

The trailer on a technical level is simply brilliant. It does what so few trailers fail to do, it manages to get us deeply involved emotionally in the story by acting as a complete introduction to the movie but clearly not revealing anything about where the story is going to lead in the end. It isn't just a series of random, flashy, meaningless jump cuts like the new Star Wars trailers. The dialogue and acting is simply perfect, very reminiscent of the quieter, more human parts from the original Ghostbusters movie. As a lifelong Ghostbusters fan, I am extremely surprised and excited and cannot wait for opening night. The REAL Ghostbusters universe will finally come back to life the way it should've many years ago!
